Program History (The Pointless Bit!)


Version 1.00 (30.08.1996)

First Release. Released on CU Amiga CD-Rom 6.
                                                               

Version 1.10 (07.06.1997 released 10.10.1997)

Arbitary limit of 500 worms levels increased to 1000.
Checking included for 1000 level limit (so it won't crash out!)
You don't need the Worms: assign if WormLevs is run from the Worms dir.
Compiled with a later version of the compiler (takes up a lot less disk
space, 23k instead of 49k!!, even with the extra goodies)
E-Mail address included.
Professional title screen ;-)
Version string information in main executable (very handy, not...)
Now uses AmigaDOS copy command to copy files instead of messy AMOS code.
(That does however mean that you cannot have a space character in the path)
Deletes levels from previous run automatically (no need to mess around
with scripts)
Now with automatic TWCustom/Storage setup - no need to do it yourself!
Can now specify how many levels to copy via the command line.






















